main event: A civilian witnessed multiple highly illuminated and maneuverable objects near Dayton, Ohio on January 5 or 6, 1964.
interesting points: The witness called to report the sighting but did not provide any additional details.
The objects were seen about 10 miles west of Dayton.
The report was inconclusive, with the case being listed as "Unknown".
The sighting was reported to the Air Force's Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO reports.
sighted object: multiple highly illuminated and maneuverable objects
photographs: yes, but not included in the report
